<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF2D6A92FA489EF91726B223" pageId="214" pageNumber="976" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF2D6A92FA489EF91726B223" blockId="214.[1456,2665,1340,2361]" pageId="214" pageNumber="976">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF2D6A92FA489EF91913B3F3" bold="true" box="[1460,1811,2208,2241]" pageId="214" pageNumber="976">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Reddish 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF2D6A92FA0B9E911850B3DB" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[1527,1616,2248,2281]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="214" pageNumber="976" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
is currently known from only a few specimens and is likely a rare montane species. Virtually nothing is known aboutits ecology or threats.
</paragraph>
